Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Add the @peas{120%g} to the saucepan to cook for the final ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the saucepan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

While the rice cooks, trim the @green beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a medium #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @British Beef Mince{240%g} to the green beans and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the beef is browned, add the garlic to the frying pan and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @teriyaki sauce{150%ml} and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed, adding a splash of @water{} if it's a little dry.

Fluff up the rice using a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the teriyaki beef stir-fry.

Enjoy!